race.description: Queanbeyan Leagues Country Boosted Mdn Hcp
race.comment: Tough. MARY LE BONE (7) missed a whisker at Goulburn but has disappointed the two since. Is on a quick backup and draws low. Wins at best and it won't surprise to see him bounce back in this company. HELLCAT (6) is in the local who made good improvement placing at Canberra but didn't finish the race off at Moruya over a mile following. Better placed at home back in trip and gets in well with the 2kg claim. YINDYAMARRA (3) resumed at Canberra and needed the outing. Has both the tongue tie and winkers applied for the first time and draws well. Showed enough on debut to consider. HONEST WARRIOR (2) is a local third-up and capable of improvement. BULLECOURT (1) has the blinkers on for the first time and can show more returning from a spell.
